# The Dependency Array

`useEffect` accepts a second argument: an array of dependencies. React will only re‑run the effect if one of the dependencies has changed since the last render.

## Three Patterns

1. **No array** – runs after every render.
2. **Empty array `[]`** – runs only once after the initial mount.
3. **Array with values `[dep1, dep2]`** – runs when any dependency changes.

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  // Runs only on mount
}, []);

useEffect(() => {
  // Runs when `userId` changes
}, [userId]);
```

slides.codeSnippet:
useEffect(() => {
  console.log('Component mounted');
  // Fetch data here
}, []);

// This will only log once, after initial render.
